name: Mahesh Bhatt
text: Then as he bid us goodbye he folded his hands and thanked us for bringing the problem to his attention by criticising his government in our press conference.  The warmth of his smile still lingers in my heart. Goodbye Sir üôèüôèüôè

name: Mahesh Bhatt
text: Next day as we sat face to face with him. Within minutes of our presentation of the picture of the crisis he ordered his administration to give all displaced families of Kargil 6 months‚Äô rations in one go so that they could face the harsh winters of that region!

name: Mahesh Bhatt
text:
As our story hit the headlines, the very next day I got a call from Vajpayee ji himself! 
In a deeply concerned voice he asked me to come to Delhi immediately with Kargil people, saying together we would find a way to resolving their problem. And, this is exactly what he did!

name: Mahesh Bhatt
text: In 1999, when the nation was preparing for a new century. I addressed a press conference in Delhi with people displaced by the war in Kargil. Who were staring at one of the most miserable winters with nothing to eat as their crops had been destroyed by the war.

name: Mahesh Bhatt
text:
From my personal experience, I can vouch that in the past couple of decades there has never been a more empathetic political leader in India than Vajpayee ji!. He belonged to a different class of politician that this country no longer produces, 
We will deeply miss you, Sir! RIP.
